@startuml Fig_3_4_4_Transformer_Multi_Head_Attention
title Fig 3.4.4: Multi-Head Causal Self-Attention (CausalSelfAttention)\n— QKV fusion + scaled dot-product attention

skinparam backgroundColor #FEFEFE
skinparam rectangleBackgroundColor #F5F5FF

rectangle "Input **x**\nshape (B, T, C)\nC = n_embd" as X

rectangle "**Linear QKV**\nW_qkv : C → 3C" as QKV
X --> QKV

rectangle "Split & reshape\n**Q, K, V**\n(B, n_heads, T, head_dim)" as SPLIT
QKV --> SPLIT

rectangle "Optional **KV cache**\nconcat past K,V along T" as CACHE
SPLIT --> CACHE

rectangle "**scaled_dot_product_attention**\n(PyTorch SDPA / Flash)\n**is_causal** = True (train)\nFalse (cached decode)" as SDPA
CACHE --> SDPA

rectangle "Merge heads\n(B, T, C)" as MERGE
SDPA --> MERGE

rectangle "**Output proj**\nW_o : C → C\n+ dropout" as OUT
MERGE --> OUT

rectangle "Output **y**\n(B, T, C)" as Y
OUT --> Y

note bottom of SDPA
  **head_dim** = C / n_heads\n**Attention(Q,K,V)** = softmax(QK^T / √d) V\nCausal mask prevents attending to future tokens\nwhen training on full sequences
end note

@enduml
